:End Note

Note:
End-to-end probe of the v0.0.8.5 modular SEMANTIC subsystem (task #491).

This test drives the real semantic passes and asserts their behavior rather than
their mere existence:

  symbol insert + lookup       -> symbol_table_add_symbol / symbol_table_lookup_symbol
  scope nesting + shadowing    -> symbol_table_enter_scope / exit_scope, inner binding
                                  shadows the outer one then the outer one is restored
  duplicate-symbol detection   -> symbol_table_add_symbol rejects a same-scope redecl
  type-check ACCEPT            -> type_checker_check_compatibility exact + coercion
  type-check REJECT            -> type_checker_check_compatibility incompatible kinds
  pattern binding              -> collect_pattern_bindings records an identifier pattern

The Type structures are the minimal shape the type checker reads: type_id at
offset 0 and type_kind at offset 8 (see type_checker.runa check_compatibility).
The Symbol scope field lives at offset 16 and the symbol table tracks the active
scope id at table offset 16; add_symbol is therefore called with the current
scope id as its scope_level so the two number spaces agree (the convention shared
with scope_analyzer, which keeps its scope id in lockstep with the table's).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/semantic/symbol_table.runa" as SymbolTable
Import "compiler/frontend/semantic/scope_analyzer.runa" as ScopeAnalyzer
Import "compiler/frontend/semantic/type_checker.runa" as TypeChecker
Import "compiler/frontend/semantic/pattern_analyzer.runa" as PatternAnalyzer
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa" as AST
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/hashtable.runa" as HashTable
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: Symbol type and basic type-kind constants (mirrored from the modules under
Note: test for readability; the modules remain the single source of truth).
Constant SYMBOL_TYPE_VARIABLE as Integer is 1
Constant TYPE_KIND_INTEGER as Integer is 1
Constant TYPE_KIND_FLOAT as Integer is 2
Constant TYPE_KIND_STRING as Integer is 3
Constant AST_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN as Integer is 5000

Note: Build a minimal Type record: type_id at offset 0, type_kind at offset 8.
Process called "make_type" takes type_id as Integer, type_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with 160
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with t, 0, type_id
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with t, 8, type_kind
    Return t
End Process

Note: Build an identifier pattern node carrying the given name in its value field.
Process called "make_identifier_pattern" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN, 1, 1
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with node, name, 0
    Return node
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "semantic_subsystem_probe"

    Let arena be proc arena_create from Arena with 65536
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "analysis arena builds", arena

    Note: ---- Symbol table: create ----
    Let table be proc symbol_table_create from SymbolTable with arena
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "symbol table builds", table

    Note: ---- Insert + lookup in the global scope (scope id 0) ----
    Let name_x be "x"
    Let sym_x be proc symbol_table_add_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, SYMBOL_TYPE_VARIABLE, 0, 10, 1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "global x inserted", sym_x

    Let found_x be proc symbol_table_lookup_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "lookup finds the inserted x", found_x, sym_x

    Note: A name that was never declared must not be found.
    Let missing be proc symbol_table_lookup_symbol from SymbolTable with table, "nope", arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "undeclared name not found", missing, 0

    Note: ---- Duplicate-symbol detection in the same scope ----
    Let dup be proc symbol_table_add_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, SYMBOL_TYPE_VARIABLE, 0, 11, 1
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "duplicate x in same scope rejected", dup, 0

    Note: ---- Scope nesting + shadowing ----
    Let inner_scope be proc symbol_table_enter_scope from SymbolTable with table, 2, 12
    proc assert_true from TestUtils with results, "entered an inner scope", inner_scope

    Note: Declaring x in the inner scope shadows the global x (not a duplicate).
    Let inner_x be proc symbol_table_add_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, SYMBOL_TYPE_VARIABLE, inner_scope, 13, 1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "inner x inserted (shadows global)", inner_x

    Note: From the inner scope, lookup must resolve to the inner binding.
    Let inner_found be proc symbol_table_lookup_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "inner lookup sees inner x", inner_found, inner_x

    Note: Leaving the scope restores the outer binding.
    proc symbol_table_exit_scope from SymbolTable with table
    Let outer_again be proc symbol_table_lookup_symbol from SymbolTable with table, name_x, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "after exit, lookup sees global x again", outer_again, sym_x

    Note: ---- Type checker: ACCEPT cases ----
    Let scope_analyzer be proc scope_analyzer_create from ScopeAnalyzer with table, arena
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "scope analyzer builds", scope_analyzer

    Let checker be proc type_checker_create from TypeChecker with table, scope_analyzer, arena
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "type checker builds", checker

    Note: Identical type ids = exact match (compatibility level 3).
    Let int_a be proc make_type with 100, TYPE_KIND_INTEGER
    Let int_b be proc make_type with 100, TYPE_KIND_INTEGER
    Let exact be proc type_checker_check_compatibility from TypeChecker with checker, int_a, int_b, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "Integer vs Integer is exact (3)", exact, 3

    Note: Integer (kind 1) coerces to Float (kind 2) = level 2.
    Let int_c be proc make_type with 101, TYPE_KIND_INTEGER
    Let flt be proc make_type with 102, TYPE_KIND_FLOAT
    Let coerce be proc type_checker_check_compatibility from TypeChecker with checker, int_c, flt, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "Integer coerces to Float (2)", coerce, 2

    Note: ---- Type checker: REJECT case ----
    Note: String (kind 3) and Integer (kind 1) share no compatibility relation.
    Let str_t be proc make_type with 103, TYPE_KIND_STRING
    Let int_d be proc make_type with 104, TYPE_KIND_INTEGER
    Let incompatible be proc type_checker_check_compatibility from TypeChecker with checker, str_t, int_d, arena
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "String vs Integer is incompatible (0)", incompatible, 0

    Note: ---- Pattern binding ----
    Let pattern_analyzer be proc create_pattern_analyzer from PatternAnalyzer with checker, table, scope_analyzer
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "pattern analyzer builds", pattern_analyzer

    Let pattern be proc make_identifier_pattern with "y"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "identifier pattern builds", pattern

    Note: collect_pattern_bindings records the binding into a name-keyed hashtable.
    Let bm be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "binding map builds", bm

    Let collect_ok be proc collect_pattern_bindings from PatternAnalyzer with pattern_analyzer, pattern, bm
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "identifier pattern binding collected", collect_ok, 1

    Note: The collected binding must be retrievable from the map by its name.
    Let bound be proc hashtable_has from HashTable with bm, "y"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "binding 'y' recorded in map", bound, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
